## Constraints
*   Customers must be logged in to update addresses.
*   Customers must have at least one saved address.
*   Only one primary address allowed at any given time.
## Assumptions
*   Customers often have multiple addresses (home, office, relatives).
*   Customers expect checkout to default to the primary address.
*   Deleting an address removes all associated metadata (including primary flag).
## Acceptance Criteria

| **AC ID** | **Acceptance Criteria** | **Details / Expected Outcome** |
| ---| ---| --- |
| AC-PSA-01 | Primary Address Selection | When a customer clicks **“Set as Primary Address”** on a saved address card, that address is marked as the primary address. |
| AC-PSA-02 | Confirmation Feedback | After setting the primary address, the system displays a success toast message: **“Successfully updated Primary Address.”** |
| AC-PSA-03 | Primary Address Labeling | The system displays a **“Primary Address” tag** within the chosen address card. |
| AC-PSA-04 | UI Update – Hide Action | The **“Set as Primary Address”** link is hidden from the card that is already marked as primary. |
| AC-PSA-05 | UI Update – Non-Primary Addresses | All other address cards continue to show the **“Set as Primary Address”** link. |
| AC-PSA-06 | Switching Primary Addresses | If another address is selected as primary, it replaces the previously set primary address. |
| AC-PSA-07 | No Primary Address Case | If no primary address is set, all addresses show the **“Set as Primary Address”** link, and no “Primary Address” tag is displayed. |
| AC-PSA-08 | Single Address Case | If the customer has only one address, the system automatically marks it as primary and hides the **“Set as Primary Address”** link. |
| AC-PSA-09 | Persistence | The selected primary address remains stored and is displayed correctly even after page refresh or customer re-login. |

